#
# BedrockOnLinux — install & run Minecraft Bedrock (Windows GDK build) on any
# Linux. One app, everything bundled. CLI + graphical launcher.
#
# SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
#
# The launcher lets you, before playing:
#   * pick & download the Minecraft version (stable or beta),
#   * pick the GDK-Proton version (auto-patched so the game runs),
#   * pick / auto-match the ProxyPass build,
#   * sign in to Microsoft (device code surfaced in the UI),
#   * set the server IP/port to connect to (ProxyPass relay),
# then Play. ProxyPass runs in the background; in game you join the LAN game
